{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G1NwY8kHdyJ7aE8CkP3CoL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# FINDINGS SUMMARY: Idea 3 — End-to-End Calibration via Direct E2E Objective\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-02-27\n     4→**Status:** Partially successful — CMA-ES achieves 15.1% mean E2E with 4/10 < 10%; specific models (codellama-34b, llama-2-70b) reach production quality\n     5→\n     6→## 1. Idea Recap\n     7→\n     8→This idea jointly calibrates all LatencyModel coefficients by directly minimizing BLIS E2E mean error using CMA-ES (Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy), bypassing per-component accuracy. The approach treats BLIS as a black-box function mapping artifact parameters → E2E error and optimizes per-model coefficient vectors (~16-23 parameters) against trace-replay experiments.\n     9→\n    10→**Starting point:** Round 2's best regime ensemble artifacts with the overhead floor mechanism (56.2% mean E2E with trace replay, 9.5% mean ITL).\n    11→\n    12→**Key insight:** Per-step MAPE is a poor proxy for E2E error (Round 2: 64.4% step → 427.8% E2E). This idea optimizes E2E *directly* rather than using step accuracy as an intermediate.\n    13→\n    14→## 2. Sub-Hypothesis Results Table\n    15→\n    16→| Sub-Hypothesis | Status | Key Metric | Takeaway |\n    17→|---|---|---|---|\n    18→| **H1:** CMA-ES + trace replay → < 15% E2E | **PARTIALLY SUPPORTED** | E2E 15.1% (target < 15%) | 3.7x improvement; 4/10 < 10%; narrowly missed target |\n    19→| **H2:** Workload-spec mode → < 50% E2E | **NOT TESTED** | All BLIS runs failed | Profile file mismatch between repos; infrastructure gap |\n    20→| **H3:** Additive corrections → -5pp E2E | **REFUTED for E2E** | E2E 17.2% (+2.1pp worse) | Corrections conflict with CMA-ES absorption; TTFT improved to 9.4% |\n    21→\n    22→## 3. Best BLIS E2E Result — Full Per-Experiment Error Table\n    23→\n    24→**H1 results (CMA-ES + trace replay):**\n    25→\n    26→| Experiment | Model | Workload | GT E2E (ms) | BLIS E2E (ms) | E2E Error | TTFT Error | ITL Error |\n    27→|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n    28→| llama-2-7b-tp1-roleplay | llama-2-7b | roleplay | 2,071 | 1,612 | 22.2% | 60.8% | 91.1% |\n    29→| llama-2-70b-tp4-general | llama-2-70b | general | 5,321 | 4,458 | 16.2% | 82.5% | 72.0% |\n    30→| llama-2-70b-hf-tp4-codegen | llama-2-70b-hf | codegen | 4,606 | 4,432 | **3.8%** | 67.6% | 111.6% |\n    31→| llama-2-70b-tp4-roleplay | llama-2-70b | roleplay | 4,562 | 4,249 | **6.9%** | 67.6% | 117.0% |\n    32→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-codegen | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | codegen | 4,675 | 3,229 | 30.9% | 66.4% | 41.5% |\n    33→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-general | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | general | 5,039 | 4,399 | 12.7% | 57.3% | 78.1% |\n    34→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-roleplay | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | roleplay | 4,685 | 3,084 | 34.2% | 69.3% | 34.5% |\n    35→| codellama-34b-tp2-general | codellama-34b | general | 4,093 | 4,044 | **1.2%** | 69.3% | 102.7% |\n    36→| codellama-34b-tp2-codegen | codellama-34b | codegen | 3,723 | 3,536 | **5.0%** | 68.9% | 90.2% |\n    37→| codellama-34b-tp2-roleplay | codellama-34b | roleplay | 3,670 | 3,028 | 17.5% | 66.2% | 135.4% |\n    38→| **MEAN** | | | | | **15.1%** | **67.6%** | **87.4%** |\n    39→\n    40→**Best per-model CMA-ES results (optimization across workloads):**\n    41→\n    42→| Model | Initial E2E | Optimized E2E | Improvement |\n    43→|---|---|---|---|\n    44→| llama-2-7b | 60.9% | 22.2% | 2.7x |\n    45→| llama-2-70b | 58.2% avg | **8.3%** | 7.0x |\n    46→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 53.0% avg | 25.9% | 2.0x |\n    47→| codellama-34b | 55.8% avg | **7.9%** | 7.1x |\n    48→\n    49→## 4. What Worked (Specific Techniques)\n    50→\n    51→1. **CMA-ES for black-box DES calibration** — Treating BLIS as a black-box function and optimizing against E2E directly was effective. CMA-ES found parameter settings that reduce E2E error 2-7x per model, despite noisy multi-experiment objectives and ~20 parameters.\n    52→\n    53→2. **Per-model optimization** — Mandatory. Each model has fundamentally different step-time characteristics (7B: 3.9ms overhead, Mixtral: 9.1ms overhead). A single global optimization would fail.\n    54→\n    55→3. **Overhead floor as the primary knob** — The step_overhead_us parameter (overhead floor) controls the dominant timing characteristic. CMA-ES consistently tuned this upward (e.g., llama-2-7b: 3,897 → 5,051μs, +30%) to match real vLLM step cycle times.\n    56→\n    57→4. **Scheduling time as secondary knob** — For larger models (llama-2-70b), scheduling_processing_time_us doubled (415 → 821μs), capturing CPU overhead that the step-time model misses.\n    58→\n    59→5. **TTFT additive corrections (H3)** — While not helpful for E2E, applying per-model additive corrections to QueueingTime reduced TTFT error from 67.6% → 9.4%. This is the first time TTFT has been below 10% in this research.\n    60→\n    61→## 5. What Failed and Why (Root Causes)\n    62→\n    63→1. **E2E optimization sacrifices ITL accuracy** — CMA-ES optimizes the E2E objective, which can increase per-token overhead (output_token_processing_time_us) to match total E2E at the expense of ITL accuracy. ITL worsened from 9.5% → 87.4%. This is the fundamental tension: E2E = TTFT + Σ(ITL), so optimizing total while ignoring components produces imbalanced solutions.\n    64→\n    65→2. **Mixtral and llama-2-7b resist optimization** — These models achieved only 25.9% and 22.2% E2E respectively, vs. 8.3% and 7.9% for the others. Root causes:\n    66→   - **llama-2-7b:** Only 1 experiment (roleplay). CMA-ES has no cross-workload validation and may overfit.\n    67→   - **Mixtral:** MoE architecture has higher per-step variance and less predictable batch behavior.\n    68→\n    69→3. **H2 (workload-spec mode) completely failed** — Profile file mismatch between BLIS-research and inference-sim repos. The experiment directory naming conventions differ, preventing automatic matching.\n    70→\n    71→4. **H3 corrections conflict with H1 optimization** — CMA-ES already \"absorbed\" the TTFT deficit into its coefficient values. Applying post-hoc TTFT corrections double-counts the adjustment, worsening E2E by 2.1pp.\n    72→\n    73→## 6. Binding Constraints\n    74→\n    75→| Constraint | Status | Evidence |\n    76→|---|---|---|\n    77→| **BC-1: TTFT/simulation fidelity mismatch** | Partially resolved by H3 | TTFT 9.4% with corrections; 67.6% without |\n    78→| **BC-NEW: E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff** | **NEW BINDING CONSTRAINT** | Optimizing E2E worsens ITL (9.5% → 87.4%). Cannot optimize both with the same coefficient set. |\n    79→| **BC-2: KV feature scaling** | Not addressed | KV features are in the artifact but CMA-ES doesn't specifically target them |\n    80→| **BC-3: CodeLlama-34B anomaly** | Resolved | E2E 7.9% mean — CMA-ES found good coefficients for this model |\n    81→| **BC-4: Mixtral MoE variance** | Partially addressed | 25.9% mean — better than baseline but above target |\n    82→\n    83→## 7. Data Insights Discovered\n    84→\n    85→1. **E2E and ITL are in tension.** The LatencyModel interface has 5 methods that all contribute to E2E, but their contributions are nonlinearly coupled through simulation dynamics (queueing, batch formation). Optimizing total E2E via coefficient tuning can achieve good E2E by offsetting errors across methods — but this produces arbitrarily bad per-method metrics.\n    86→\n    87→2. **CMA-ES convergence is model-dependent.** Larger models (70B, 34B) converge faster to low E2E because they have more experiments (3 each) providing a smoother objective landscape. llama-2-7b (1 experiment) converges slowly and to a worse optimum.\n    88→\n    89→3. **The overhead floor works bidirectionally.** CMA-ES sometimes *decreased* step_overhead_us (codellama-34b: 6,673 → 5,998, -10%) while increasing scheduling time. This suggests the initial overhead floor was already close to optimal for some models, and the remaining error is in secondary method timing.\n    90→\n    91→4. **TTFT bias is systematic and model-independent.** All models under-predict TTFT by 3-4x (60-83% error). This is a simulation-level characteristic, not a step-time model issue. The additive correction (16-61ms per model) fully compensates.\n    92→\n    93→5. **Output token processing time is the hidden parameter.** CMA-ES increased output_token_processing_time_us dramatically for llama-2-7b (0 → 1,899μs). This effectively adds ~1.9ms per output token, which is physically implausible but mathematically optimal for E2E. This reveals that the LatencyModel interface lacks a \"simulation overhead\" parameter — the optimizer uses OutputTokenProcessingTime as a proxy for missing dynamics.\n    94→\n    95→## 8. Comparison to Baseline\n    96→\n    97→| Metric | R2 Workload-Spec | R3 Idea 1 (Trace) | R3 Idea 3 H1 (CMA-ES) | R3 Idea 3 H3 (Corrections) |\n    98→|---|---|---|---|---|\n    99→| Mean E2E error | 427.8% | 56.2% | **15.1%** | 17.2% |\n   100→| Mean TTFT error | 31,906% | 78.8% | 67.6% | **9.4%** |\n   101→| Mean ITL error | 33.6% | **9.5%** | 87.4% | 81.1% |\n   102→| E2E < 10% | 1/10 | 0/10 | **4/10** | 4/10 |\n   103→| E2E < 15% | — | 0/10 | **5/10** | 4/10 |\n   104→\n   105→**Net assessment:** CMA-ES E2E optimization achieves the best E2E accuracy in the research program (15.1% mean, 4/10 < 10%). However, it sacrifices ITL accuracy and TTFT accuracy to achieve this. The combination of H1 (E2E optimization) + H3 (TTFT correction) produces the most balanced result: 17.2% E2E + 9.4% TTFT, but ITL remains at 81.1%.\n   106→\n   107→## 9. Go Integration Feasibility\n   108→\n   109→**Already integrated.** The Go changes needed for this experiment were:\n   110→\n   111→| File | Change | Lines |\n   112→|---|---|---|\n   113→| `sim/config.go` | Added `StepMLModelPath` field + `WithStepMLModel` builder | ~12 |\n   114→| `sim/latency/latency.go` | Added StepML dispatch in factory (after roofline, before blackbox) | ~7 |\n   115→| `cmd/root.go` | Added `--stepml-model` CLI flag + wiring | ~8 |\n   116→\n   117→Total: ~27 lines of Go changes. The optimized artifacts use the same JSON schema as the Round 2 artifacts and load through the existing `sim/latency/stepml.go` evaluator unchanged.\n   118→\n   119→**Artifact format:** Standard StepML JSON with version 2, step_time_regimes, and calibrated overhead/secondary method values. No new fields needed.\n   120→\n   121→**Performance:** Each BLIS simulation run with StepML takes 2-10 seconds (depending on experiment size). The CMA-ES optimization requires 96-152 evaluations per model, totaling ~30 minutes per model.\n   122→\n   123→## 10. Generalization Results\n   124→\n   125→### H4: Leave-One-Workload-Out (LOWO) — Part A Per-Workload Breakdown\n   126→\n   127→**Status: PARTIALLY SUPPORTED**\n   128→\n   129→CMA-ES-optimized artifacts evaluated per-workload:\n   130→\n   131→| Model Group | Codegen | General | Roleplay | Range (pp) | Mean |\n   132→|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n   133→| llama-2-7b | — | — | 22.2% | — | 22.2% |\n   134→| llama-2-70b | **3.8%** | 16.2% | **6.9%** | 12.4 | 9.0% |\n   135→| codellama-34b | **5.0%** | **1.2%** | 17.5% | 16.3 | 7.9% |\n   136→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 30.9% | 12.7% | 34.2% | 21.5 | 25.9% |\n   137→\n   138→Dense models generalize well across workloads (9-16pp range). Mixtral shows highest workload variance (21.5pp). 8/10 experiments within 2x of aggregate (15.1%), but mixtral-roleplay (34.2%) slightly exceeds. Part B (LOWO CMA-ES re-optimization) not tested (requires ~4.5 hours of CMA-ES runs).\n   139→\n   140→### H5: Leave-One-Model-Out (LOMO) — Cross-Model Artifact Transfer\n   141→\n   142→**Status: SUPPORTED** — Mean best-donor E2E = **14.8%** (threshold <50%)\n   143→\n   144→Cross-model transfer matrix (E2E %):\n   145→\n   146→| Donor → Target | codellama-34b | llama-2-70b | llama-2-7b | mixtral-8x7b |\n   147→|---|---|---|---|---|\n   148→| codellama-34b | — | 21.2% | 24.3% | 21.2% |\n   149→| llama-2-70b | 24.7% | — | 94.0% | **5.1%** |\n   150→| llama-2-7b | 40.4% | 53.8% | — | 53.8% |\n   151→| mixtral-8x7b | **11.9%** | 26.0% | **20.9%** | — |\n   152→\n   153→**Best donor per target:**\n   154→- codellama-34b ← mixtral (11.9%)\n   155→- llama-2-70b ← codellama-34b (21.2%)\n   156→- llama-2-7b ← mixtral (20.9%)\n   157→- mixtral ← llama-2-70b (**5.1%**)\n   158→\n   159→**Key insight:** CMA-ES artifacts have dramatically better cross-model transfer than per-step models because they capture simulation-level dynamics (overhead floor, scheduling overhead) that are partially model-independent. Mixtral is the best universal donor; 70B→Mixtral transfer (5.1%) actually outperforms Mixtral's own in-distribution result (25.9%).\n   160→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YDgwzYnaKyFjGGak7aDXLb","session_id":"c72182bb-90d4-4f72-be1e-6f3d8138bce2","uuid":"f33f7f1f-fbc9-4a48-848e-17be741ef766"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LyfeUhYPw6pmHjewwFj2Bx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# FINDINGS: H1 — Trace Replay + E2E Optimization Baseline\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-02-27\n     4→**Status:** PARTIALLY SUPPORTED\n     5→\n     6→## Claim\n     7→\n     8→CMA-ES optimization of StepML artifact parameters against BLIS E2E mean error (using trace replay) achieves < 15% mean E2E error across all experiments.\n     9→\n    10→## Result\n    11→\n    12→**Mean E2E error: 15.1%** (target < 15%). 4/10 experiments < 10%, 5/10 < 15%, 8/10 < 25%.\n    13→\n    14→The target was narrowly missed at 15.1%, but the improvement from the 56.2% baseline is dramatic (3.7x).\n    15→\n    16→## Per-Experiment Results\n    17→\n    18→| Experiment | Model | Workload | GT E2E (ms) | BLIS E2E (ms) | E2E Error | TTFT Error | ITL Error |\n    19→|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n    20→| llama-2-7b-tp1-roleplay | llama-2-7b | roleplay | 2,071 | 1,612 | **22.2%** | 60.8% | 91.1% |\n    21→| llama-2-70b-tp4-general | llama-2-70b | general | 5,321 | 4,458 | 16.2% | 82.5% | 72.0% |\n    22→| llama-2-70b-hf-tp4-codegen | llama-2-70b-hf | codegen | 4,606 | 4,432 | **3.8%** | 67.6% | 111.6% |\n    23→| llama-2-70b-tp4-roleplay | llama-2-70b | roleplay | 4,562 | 4,249 | **6.9%** | 67.6% | 117.0% |\n    24→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-codegen | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | codegen | 4,675 | 3,229 | 30.9% | 66.4% | 41.5% |\n    25→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-general | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | general | 5,039 | 4,399 | 12.7% | 57.3% | 78.1% |\n    26→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-roleplay | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | roleplay | 4,685 | 3,084 | 34.2% | 69.3% | 34.5% |\n    27→| codellama-34b-tp2-general | codellama-34b | general | 4,093 | 4,044 | **1.2%** | 69.3% | 102.7% |\n    28→| codellama-34b-tp2-codegen | codellama-34b | codegen | 3,723 | 3,536 | **5.0%** | 68.9% | 90.2% |\n    29→| codellama-34b-tp2-roleplay | codellama-34b | roleplay | 3,670 | 3,028 | 17.5% | 66.2% | 135.4% |\n    30→| **MEAN** | | | | | **15.1%** | **67.6%** | **87.4%** |\n    31→\n    32→## CMA-ES Optimization Results Per Model\n    33→\n    34→| Model | Initial E2E | Optimized E2E | Evals | Time (s) | Key Parameter Change |\n    35→|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n    36→| llama-2-7b | 60.9% | 22.2% | 152 | 801 | step_overhead_us: 3,897 → 5,051 (+30%) |\n    37→| llama-2-70b | 62.7% | 8.3% | 96 | 1,904 | scheduling_time: 415 → 821 (+98%) |\n    38→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 52.2% | 25.9% | 96 | 1,870 | step_overhead_us: 9,125 → 9,884 (+8%) |\n    39→| codellama-34b | 58.9% | 7.9% | 96 | 1,913 | step_overhead_us: 6,673 → 5,998 (-10%) |\n    40→\n    41→## Key Findings\n    42→\n    43→1. **Step overhead is the primary knob:** The optimizer consistently increased step_overhead_us (llama-2-7b: +30%), scheduling_processing_time_us (llama-2-70b: +98%), and output_token_processing_time_us to slow down simulation speed to match reality.\n    44→\n    45→2. **Model-dependent response to optimization:** llama-2-70b and codellama-34b responded best (8.3% and 7.9% mean E2E), while llama-2-7b (22.2%) and mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 (25.9%) showed limited improvement.\n    46→\n    47→3. **E2E improvement comes at ITL cost:** ITL error worsened from 9.5% → 87.4% because the optimizer increased per-token overhead to match total E2E, overshooting per-token timing. The optimizer prioritizes the E2E objective, not ITL.\n    48→\n    49→4. **TTFT remains systematically under-predicted (67.6%):** Even with optimized coefficients, BLIS TTFT is 3-5x lower than ground truth. This confirms TTFT is dominated by simulation scheduling behavior, not coefficient values.\n    50→\n    51→5. **Workload variance within a model:** For mixtral, codegen (30.9%) and roleplay (34.2%) have much higher error than general (12.7%), suggesting the optimizer overfits to the general workload.\n    52→\n    53→## Refutation Assessment\n    54→\n    55→- **Supported:** 5/10 experiments < 15% (not \"at least 5/10 < 10%\" as claimed)\n    56→- **Partially refuted:** Mean E2E = 15.1%, narrowly missing the < 15% target\n    57→- **Root cause of remaining error:** Mixtral and llama-2-7b contribute disproportionately. These models have fewer experiments (1 for llama-2-7b, 3 for mixtral) and the CMA-ES optimization is more prone to local minima.\n    58→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YDgwzYnaKyFjGGak7aDXLb","session_id":"c72182bb-90d4-4f72-be1e-6f3d8138bce2","uuid":"80b1c8fe-f137-4edb-a44d-72bb24a1e58b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HRvKKY5BHZFeyhCy9F74cE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"Round 3, Idea 3: End-to-End Calibration via Direct E2E Objective.\n     3→\n     4→Runs all three sub-hypotheses:\n     5→  H1: CMA-ES optimization of StepML parameters against BLIS E2E error (trace replay)\n     6→  H2: Same optimization in workload-spec mode\n     7→  H3: Additive correction factors for TTFT/ITL residuals\n     8→\n     9→Uses Round 2's best StepML artifacts as starting point (regime ensemble + overheads).\n    10→CMA-ES treats BLIS as a black-box function: params → E2E error.\n    11→\"\"\"\n    12→\n    13→import copy\n    14→import csv\n    15→import json\n    16→import math\n    17→import os\n    18→import random\n    19→import subprocess\n    20→import sys\n    21→import tempfile\n    22→import time\n    23→\n    24→import cma\n    25→import numpy as np\n    26→import yaml\n    27→\n    28→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    29→# Paths\n    30→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    31→SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n    32→REPO_ROOT = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n    33→PACKAGE_ROOT = \"/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package\"\n    34→BLIS_RESEARCH_ROOT = os.path.join(PACKAGE_ROOT, \"BLIS-research\")\n    35→GT_DATA_ROOT = os.path.join(BLIS_RESEARCH_ROOT, \"eval\", \"ground_truth\")\n    36→ORIG_GT_ROOT = os.path.join(PACKAGE_ROOT, \"inference-sim\", \"eval\", \"ground_truth\")\n    37→R2_ARTIFACTS_DIR = os.path.join(\n    38→    BLIS_RESEARCH_ROOT,\n    39→    \"hypotheses\", \"h-stepml\", \"round2\",\n    40→    \"idea-2-regime-ensemble\", \"h3-secondary-method-calibration\",\n    41→    \"output\", \"calibrated_artifacts\",\n    42→)\n    43→BINARY_PATH = os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, \"simulation_worker\")\n    44→BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS = 16\n    45→\n    46→# Model → artifact file mapping\n    47→MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP = {\n    48→    \"llama-2-7b\": \"llama-2-7b_tp1_regime.json\",\n    49→    \"llama-2-70b\": \"llama-2-70b_tp4_regime.json\",\n    50→    \"llama-2-70b-hf\": \"llama-2-70b-hf_tp4_regime.json\",\n    51→    \"codellama-34b\": \"codellama-34b_tp2_regime.json\",\n    52→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1_tp2_regime.json\",\n    53→}\n    54→\n    55→# Models that share the same artifact (grouped for optimization)\n    56→MODEL_GROUPS = {\n    57→    \"llama-2-7b\": [\"llama-2-7b\"],\n    58→    \"llama-2-70b\": [\"llama-2-70b\", \"llama-2-70b-hf\"],\n    59→    \"codellama-34b\": [\"codellama-34b\"],\n    60→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": [\"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\"],\n    61→}\n    62→\n    63→\n    64→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    65→# Helpers (reused from Idea 1)\n    66→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    67→def parse_experiment_dir(dirname):\n    68→    import re\n    69→    tp_matches = list(re.finditer(r\"-tp(\\d+)-\", dirname))\n    70→    if not tp_matches:\n    71→        raise ValueError(f\"Cannot parse: {dirname}\")\n    72→    last_tp = tp_matches[-1]\n    73→    if re.match(r\"^\\d{8}-\\d{6}-\", dirname):\n    74→        model = dirname[16:last_tp.start()]\n    75→    elif re.match(r\"^\\d{8}-\", dirname):\n    76→        model = dirname[9:last_tp.start()]\n    77→    else:\n    78→        model = dirname[:last_tp.start()]\n    79→    return {\n    80→        \"model\": model,\n    81→        \"tp\": int(last_tp.group(1)),\n    82→        \"workload\": dirname[last_tp.end():],\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→\n    86→def load_ground_truth(experiment_dir):\n    87→    summary_path = os.path.join(\n    88→        experiment_dir, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n    89→    )\n    90→    with open(summary_path) as f:\n    91→        data = json.load(f)\n    92→    successes = data.get(\"successes\", {})\n    93→    latency = successes.get(\"latency\", {})\n    94→    return {\n    95→        \"e2e_mean_s\": latency.get(\"request_latency\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n    96→        \"ttft_mean_s\": latency.get(\"time_to_first_token\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n    97→        \"itl_mean_s\": latency.get(\"inter_token_latency\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n    98→        \"num_requests\": data.get(\"load_summary\", {}).get(\"count\", 0),\n    99→        \"prompt_len_mean\": successes.get(\"prompt_len\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n   100→        \"output_len_mean\": successes.get(\"output_len\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n   101→        \"throughput_rps\": successes.get(\"throughput\", {}).get(\"requests_per_sec\", 0),\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→\n   105→def load_exp_config(experiment_dir):\n   106→    with open(os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"exp-config.yaml\")) as f:\n   107→        return yaml.safe_load(f)\n   108→\n   109→\n   110→def extract_kv_blocks(experiment_dir):\n   111→    import re\n   112→    vllm_log = os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"vllm.log\")\n   113→    if not os.path.isfile(vllm_log):\n   114→        return None\n   115→    pattern = re.compile(r\"GPU KV cache size:\\s+([\\d,]+)\\s+tokens\")\n   116→    with open(vllm_log) as f:\n   117→        for line in f:\n   118→            m = pattern.search(line)\n   119→            if m:\n   120→                return int(m.group(1).replace(\",\", \"\")) // BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS\n   121→    return None\n   122→\n   123→\n   124→def extract_cpu_kv_blocks(experiment_dir):\n   125→    import re\n   126→    vllm_log = os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"vllm.log\")\n   127→    if not os.path.isfile(vllm_log):\n   128→        return 0\n   129→    cpu_bytes = None\n   130→    kv_shape = None\n   131→    with open(vllm_log) as f:\n   132→        for line in f:\n   133→            m = re.search(r\"cpu_bytes_to_use['\\\"]?:\\s*([\\d.]+)\", line)\n   134→            if m and cpu_bytes is None:\n   135→                cpu_bytes = float(m.group(1))\n   136→            m = re.search(\n   137→                r\"cross layer KV cache of shape \\((\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+)\\)\",\n   138→                line,\n   139→            )\n   140→            if m and kv_shape is None:\n   141→                kv_shape = tuple(int(m.group(i)) for i in range(1, 7))\n   142→    if cpu_bytes is None or kv_shape is None or cpu_bytes == 0:\n   143→        return 0\n   144→    _, num_layers, _, block_size, num_kv_heads, head_dim = kv_shape\n   145→    per_block_bytes = num_layers * 2 * block_size * num_kv_heads * head_dim * 2\n   146→    return int(cpu_bytes) // per_block_bytes\n   147→\n   148→\n   149→def convert_lifecycle_to_csv(lifecycle_path, output_csv, model_name, seed=42):\n   150→    with open(lifecycle_path) as f:\n   151→        data = json.load(f)\n   152→    if not data:\n   153→        raise ValueError(f\"Empty lifecycle data: {lifecycle_path}\")\n   154→    rng = random.Random(seed)\n   155→    base_time = min(entry[\"start_time\"] for entry in data)\n   156→    rows = []\n   157→    for i, entry in enumerate(data):\n   158→        info = entry.get(\"info\", {})\n   159→        input_count = info.get(\"input_tokens\", 0)\n   160→        output_count = info.get(\"output_tokens\", 0)\n   161→        arrival_s = entry[\"start_time\"] - base_time\n   162→        input_tokens = [rng.randint(0, 31999) for _ in range(input_count)]\n   163→        output_tokens = [rng.randint(0, 31999) for _ in range(output_count)]\n   164→        rows.append((arrival_s, i, model_name, input_tokens, output_tokens))\n   165→    rows.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\n   166→    with open(output_csv, \"w\") as f:\n   167→        f.write(\"arrival_time,request_id,model,prefill_tokens,decode_tokens\\n\")\n   168→        for arrival_s, req_id, model, inp, out in rows:\n   169→            f.write(\n   170→                f\"{arrival_s:.6f},request_{req_id},{model},\"\n   171→                f'\"{json.dumps(inp)}\",\"{json.dumps(out)}\"\\n'\n   172→            )\n   173→    return {\n   174→        \"num_requests\": len(rows),\n   175→        \"duration_s\": (rows[-1][0] - rows[0][0]) if len(rows) > 1 else 0,\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→\n   179→def compute_error(predicted, observed):\n   180→    if observed == 0:\n   181→        return float(\"inf\") if predicted != 0 else 0.0\n   182→    return abs(predicted - observed) / observed\n   183→\n   184→\n   185→def parse_blis_stdout(stdout):\n   186→    lines = stdout.split(\"\\n\")\n   187→    json_lines = []\n   188→    in_json = False\n   189→    brace_depth = 0\n   190→    for line in lines:\n   191→        if \"Simulation Metrics\" in line:\n   192→            in_json = False\n   193→            json_lines = []\n   194→            continue\n   195→        if not in_json and line.strip().startswith(\"{\"):\n   196→            in_json = True\n   197→        if in_json:\n   198→            json_lines.append(line)\n   199→            brace_depth += line.count(\"{\") - line.count(\"}\")\n   200→            if brace_depth <= 0:\n   201→                break\n   202→    if not json_lines:\n   203→        return None\n   204→    try:\n   205→        metrics = json.loads(\"\\n\".join(json_lines))\n   206→    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n   207→        return None\n   208→    return {\n   209→        \"e2e_mean_ms\": metrics.get(\"e2e_mean_ms\", 0),\n   210→        \"ttft_mean_ms\": metrics.get(\"ttft_mean_ms\", 0),\n   211→        \"itl_mean_ms\": metrics.get(\"itl_mean_ms\", 0),\n   212→        \"completed_requests\": metrics.get(\"completed_requests\", 0),\n   213→    }\n   214→\n   215→\n   216→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   217→# Artifact manipulation\n   218→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   219→def load_artifact(model_name):\n   220→    \"\"\"Load the Round 2 best artifact for a given model.\"\"\"\n   221→    artifact_file = MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP.get(model_name)\n   222→    if artifact_file is None:\n   223→        raise ValueError(f\"No artifact for model: {model_name}\")\n   224→    path = os.path.join(R2_ARTIFACTS_DIR, artifact_file)\n   225→    with open(path) as f:\n   226→        return json.load(f)\n   227→\n   228→\n   229→def artifact_to_param_vector(artifact):\n   230→    \"\"\"Extract optimizable parameters from a StepML artifact.\n   231→\n   232→    Parameter vector layout:\n   233→      [step_overhead_us, step_overhead_per_req_us,\n   234→       scheduling_processing_time_us, preemption_processing_time_us,\n   235→       output_token_processing_time_us,\n   236→       queueing_intercept,\n   237→       decode_only_intercept, decode_only_decode_tokens, decode_only_num_decode_reqs,\n   238→       mixed_intercept, mixed_prefill_tokens, mixed_decode_tokens,\n   239→       mixed_num_prefill_reqs, mixed_num_decode_reqs]\n   240→\n   241→    Returns (param_vector, param_names) tuple.\n   242→    \"\"\"\n   243→    params = []\n   244→    names = []\n   245→\n   246→    # Global overhead parameters\n   247→    params.append(artifact.get(\"step_overhead_us\", 0))\n   248→    names.append(\"step_overhead_us\")\n   249→\n   250→    params.append(artifact.get(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\", 0))\n   251→    names.append(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\")\n   252→\n   253→    params.append(artifact.get(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   254→    names.append(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\")\n   255→\n   256→    params.append(artifact.get(\"preemption_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   257→    names.append(\"preemption_processing_time_us\")\n   258→\n   259→    params.append(artifact.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   260→    names.append(\"output_token_processing_time_us\")\n   261→\n   262→    # Queueing time intercept\n   263→    qt = artifact.get(\"queueing_time\")\n   264→    if qt:\n   265→        params.append(qt.get(\"intercept\", 0))\n   266→    else:\n   267→        params.append(0)\n   268→    names.append(\"queueing_intercept\")\n   269→\n   270→    # Step time regime parameters\n   271→    regimes = artifact.get(\"step_time_regimes\", [])\n   272→    for regime in regimes:\n   273→        prefix = regime[\"name\"]\n   274→        model_data = regime[\"model\"]\n   275→        params.append(model_data.get(\"intercept\", 0))\n   276→        names.append(f\"{prefix}_intercept\")\n   277→\n   278→        # Extract feature coefficients in sorted order for reproducibility\n   279→        coeffs = model_data.get(\"feature_coefficients\", {})\n   280→        for feat in sorted(coeffs.keys()):\n   281→            params.append(coeffs[feat])\n   282→            names.append(f\"{prefix}_{feat}\")\n   283→\n   284→    return np.array(params, dtype=np.float64), names\n   285→\n   286→\n   287→def param_vector_to_artifact(params, names, base_artifact):\n   288→    \"\"\"Reconstruct a StepML artifact from an optimized parameter vector.\"\"\"\n   289→    artifact = copy.deepcopy(base_artifact)\n   290→    param_dict = dict(zip(names, params))\n   291→\n   292→    artifact[\"step_overhead_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"step_overhead_us\", 0))\n   293→    artifact[\"step_overhead_per_req_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\", 0))\n   294→    artifact[\"scheduling_processing_time_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   295→    artifact[\"preemption_processing_time_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"preemption_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   296→    artifact[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   297→\n   298→    # Queueing time\n   299→    qt_intercept = param_dict.get(\"queueing_intercept\", 0)\n   300→    if artifact.get(\"queueing_time\"):\n   301→        artifact[\"queueing_time\"][\"intercept\"] = qt_intercept\n   302→    else:\n   303→        artifact[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   304→            \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   305→            \"intercept\": qt_intercept,\n   306→            \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   307→        }\n   308→\n   309→    # Regime coefficients\n   310→    for regime in artifact.get(\"step_time_regimes\", []):\n   311→        prefix = regime[\"name\"]\n   312→        intercept_key = f\"{prefix}_intercept\"\n   313→        if intercept_key in param_dict:\n   314→            regime[\"model\"][\"intercept\"] = param_dict[intercept_key]\n   315→\n   316→        coeffs = regime[\"model\"].get(\"feature_coefficients\", {})\n   317→        for feat in list(coeffs.keys()):\n   318→            key = f\"{prefix}_{feat}\"\n   319→            if key in param_dict:\n   320→                coeffs[feat] = param_dict[key]\n   321→\n   322→    return artifact\n   323→\n   324→\n   325→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   326→# BLIS execution\n   327→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   328→def run_blis_trace(trace_csv, exp_config, kv_blocks, artifact_path, horizon_us,\n   329→                   cpu_kv_blocks=0):\n   330→    \"\"\"Run BLIS in trace replay mode with a StepML artifact.\"\"\"\n   331→    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   332→        results_path = f.name\n   333→    cmd = [\n   334→        BINARY_PATH, \"run\",\n   335→        \"--model\", exp_config.get(\"model\", \"unknown\"),\n   336→        \"--workload\", \"traces\",\n   337→        \"--workload-traces-filepath\", trace_csv,\n   338→        \"--tp\", str(exp_config.get(\"tensor_parallelism\", 1)),\n   339→        \"--max-model-len\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_model_len\", 4096)),\n   340→        \"--max-num-running-reqs\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_seqs\", 128)),\n   341→        \"--max-num-scheduled-tokens\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_batched_tokens\", 2048)),\n   342→        \"--total-kv-blocks\", str(kv_blocks),\n   343→        \"--block-size-in-tokens\", str(BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS),\n   344→        \"--horizon\", str(horizon_us),\n   345→        \"--alpha-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   346→        \"--beta-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   347→        \"--stepml-model\", artifact_path,\n   348→        \"--results-path\", results_path,\n   349→        \"--log\", \"error\",\n   350→    ]\n   351→    if cpu_kv_blocks > 0:\n   352→        cmd.extend([\"--kv-cpu-blocks\", str(cpu_kv_blocks)])\n   353→\n   354→    try:\n   355→        result = subprocess.run(\n   356→            cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=300,\n   357→            cwd=os.path.dirname(BINARY_PATH),\n   358→        )\n   359→    except (subprocess.TimeoutExpired, FileNotFoundError):\n   360→        return None\n   361→    finally:\n   362→        if os.path.exists(results_path):\n   363→            os.unlink(results_path)\n   364→\n   365→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   366→        return None\n   367→    return parse_blis_stdout(result.stdout)\n   368→\n   369→\n   370→def run_blis_workload_spec(spec_path, exp_config, kv_blocks, artifact_path,\n   371→                           cpu_kv_blocks=0):\n   372→    \"\"\"Run BLIS in workload-spec mode with a StepML artifact.\"\"\"\n   373→    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   374→        results_path = f.name\n   375→    cmd = [\n   376→        BINARY_PATH, \"run\",\n   377→        \"--model\", exp_config.get(\"model\", \"unknown\"),\n   378→        \"--workload-spec\", spec_path,\n   379→        \"--tp\", str(exp_config.get(\"tensor_parallelism\", 1)),\n   380→        \"--max-model-len\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_model_len\", 4096)),\n   381→        \"--max-num-running-reqs\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_seqs\", 128)),\n   382→        \"--max-num-scheduled-tokens\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_batched_tokens\", 2048)),\n   383→        \"--total-kv-blocks\", str(kv_blocks),\n   384→        \"--block-size-in-tokens\", str(BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS),\n   385→        \"--alpha-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   386→        \"--beta-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   387→        \"--stepml-model\", artifact_path,\n   388→        \"--results-path\", results_path,\n   389→        \"--log\", \"error\",\n   390→    ]\n   391→    if cpu_kv_blocks > 0:\n   392→        cmd.extend([\"--kv-cpu-blocks\", str(cpu_kv_blocks)])\n   393→\n   394→    try:\n   395→        result = subprocess.run(\n   396→            cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=300,\n   397→            cwd=os.path.dirname(BINARY_PATH),\n   398→        )\n   399→    except (subprocess.TimeoutExpired, FileNotFoundError):\n   400→        return None\n   401→    finally:\n   402→        if os.path.exists(results_path):\n   403→            os.unlink(results_path)\n   404→\n   405→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   406→        return None\n   407→    return parse_blis_stdout(result.stdout)\n   408→\n   409→\n   410→def build_workload_spec(profile, ground_truth):\n   411→    \"\"\"Build a workload-spec from inference-perf profile.\"\"\"\n   412→    data = profile.get(\"data\", {})\n   413→    load_config = profile.get(\"load\", {})\n   414→    sp = data.get(\"shared_prefix\", {})\n   415→\n   416→    stages = []\n   417→    for stage in load_config.get(\"stages\", []):\n   418→        stages.append({\"rate\": stage[\"rate\"], \"duration\": stage[\"duration\"]})\n   419→    if not stages:\n   420→        num_requests = ground_truth.get(\"num_requests\", 1000)\n   421→        rps = ground_truth.get(\"throughput_rps\", 10)\n   422→        duration = int(num_requests / rps) + 60\n   423→        stages.append({\"rate\": rps, \"duration\": duration})\n   424→\n   425→    total_duration_s = sum(s[\"duration\"] for s in stages)\n   426→    total_requests = sum(s[\"rate\"] * s[\"duration\"] for s in stages)\n   427→    horizon_us = int(total_duration_s * 1_000_000) + 60_000_000\n   428→    aggregate_rate = sum(s[\"rate\"] * s[\"duration\"] for s in stages) / total_duration_s\n   429→\n   430→    return {\n   431→        \"version\": \"2\",\n   432→        \"seed\": 42,\n   433→        \"num_requests\": int(total_requests),\n   434→        \"horizon\": horizon_us,\n   435→        \"aggregate_rate\": aggregate_rate,\n   436→        \"inference_perf\": {\n   437→            \"stages\": stages,\n   438→            \"shared_prefix\": {\n   439→                \"num_unique_system_prompts\": sp.get(\"num_unique_system_prompts\", 9),\n   440→                \"num_users_per_system_prompt\": sp.get(\"num_users_per_system_prompt\", 5),\n   441→                \"system_prompt_len\": sp.get(\"system_prompt_len\", 100),\n   442→                \"question_len\": sp.get(\"question_len\", int(ground_truth.get(\"prompt_len_mean\", 500))),\n   443→                \"output_len\": sp.get(\"output_len\", int(ground_truth.get(\"output_len_mean\", 250))),\n   444→                \"enable_multi_turn_chat\": sp.get(\"enable_multi_turn_chat\", False),\n   445→            },\n   446→        },\n   447→    }\n   448→\n   449→\n   450→def load_profile(experiment_dir):\n   451→    profile_path = os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"profile.yaml\")\n   452→    if not os.path.isfile(profile_path):\n   453→        return None\n   454→    with open(profile_path) as f:\n   455→        content = f.read()\n   456→    try:\n   457→        return json.loads(content)\n   458→    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n   459→        return yaml.safe_load(content)\n   460→\n   461→\n   462→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   463→# Experiment discovery\n   464→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   465→def discover_experiments():\n   466→    \"\"\"Find all experiments with lifecycle data.\"\"\"\n   467→    experiments = []\n   468→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(GT_DATA_ROOT)):\n   469→        dirpath = os.path.join(GT_DATA_ROOT, dirname)\n   470→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   471→            continue\n   472→        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n   473→        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n   474→            continue\n   475→        try:\n   476→            meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n   477→        except ValueError:\n   478→            continue\n   479→\n   480→        kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks(dirpath)\n   481→        if kv_blocks is None:\n   482→            continue\n   483→        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks(dirpath)\n   484→        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n   485→        gt = load_ground_truth(dirpath)\n   486→\n   487→        experiments.append({\n   488→            \"dirname\": dirname,\n   489→            \"dirpath\": dirpath,\n   490→            \"meta\": meta,\n   491→            \"lifecycle_path\": lifecycle_path,\n   492→            \"kv_blocks\": kv_blocks,\n   493→            \"cpu_kv_blocks\": cpu_kv_blocks,\n   494→            \"exp_config\": exp_config,\n   495→            \"gt\": gt,\n   496→        })\n   497→    return experiments\n   498→\n   499→\n   500→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   501→# H1: CMA-ES E2E optimization with trace replay\n   502→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   503→def run_h1(experiments, tmpdir):\n   504→    \"\"\"H1: CMA-ES optimization of StepML parameters against BLIS E2E error.\"\"\"\n   505→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   506→    print(\"H1: CMA-ES E2E Optimization with Trace Replay\")\n   507→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   508→\n   509→    # Group experiments by model for per-model optimization\n   510→    model_experiments = {}\n   511→    for exp in experiments:\n   512→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   513→        # Map to canonical model name for artifact lookup\n   514→        canonical = model\n   515→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   516→            if model in variants:\n   517→                canonical = group_key\n   518→                break\n   519→        if canonical not in model_experiments:\n   520→            model_experiments[canonical] = []\n   521→        model_experiments[canonical].append(exp)\n   522→\n   523→    # Prepare trace CSV files for all experiments\n   524→    trace_csvs = {}\n   525→    for exp in experiments:\n   526→        csv_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{exp['dirname']}_trace.csv\")\n   527→        trace_stats = convert_lifecycle_to_csv(\n   528→            exp[\"lifecycle_path\"], csv_path,\n   529→            model_name=exp[\"exp_config\"].get(\"model\", exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]),\n   530→        )\n   531→        horizon_us = int((trace_stats[\"duration_s\"] + 120) * 1_000_000)\n   532→        trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]] = (csv_path, horizon_us)\n   533→\n   534→    # Run initial baseline (Round 2 coefficients)\n   535→    print(\"\\n--- Initial Baseline (Round 2 coefficients) ---\")\n   536→    initial_results = {}\n   537→    for exp in experiments:\n   538→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   539→        artifact = load_artifact(model)\n   540→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{exp['dirname']}_initial.json\")\n   541→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   542→            json.dump(artifact, f)\n   543→        csv_path, horizon_us = trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]]\n   544→        blis = run_blis_trace(\n   545→            csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   546→            horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   547→        )\n   548→        if blis:\n   549→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   550→            initial_results[exp[\"dirname\"]] = {\n   551→                \"blis\": blis, \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   552→                \"ttft_error\": compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000),\n   553→                \"itl_error\": compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000),\n   554→            }\n   555→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   556→        else:\n   557→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: BLIS FAILED\")\n   558→\n   559→    # Per-model CMA-ES optimization\n   560→    optimized_artifacts = {}\n   561→    optimization_logs = {}\n   562→\n   563→    for canonical_model, exps in model_experiments.items():\n   564→        print(f\"\\n--- Optimizing: {canonical_model} ({len(exps)} experiments) ---\")\n   565→\n   566→        # Load base artifact\n   567→        base_artifact = load_artifact(canonical_model)\n   568→        initial_params, param_names = artifact_to_param_vector(base_artifact)\n   569→        n_params = len(initial_params)\n   570→        print(f\"  Parameters: {n_params} ({', '.join(param_names[:5])}...)\")\n   571→        print(f\"  Initial: {dict(zip(param_names[:3], initial_params[:3]))}\")\n   572→\n   573→        # Define bounds: each param can vary between 0.1x and 10x initial\n   574→        # For zero initial values, use a reasonable range\n   575→        lower_bounds = []\n   576→        upper_bounds = []\n   577→        for i, (p, name) in enumerate(zip(initial_params, param_names)):\n   578→            if \"overhead\" in name and \"per_req\" not in name:\n   579→                # Step overhead: must stay positive, allow wide range\n   580→                lower_bounds.append(max(500, p * 0.3))\n   581→                upper_bounds.append(p * 5.0)\n   582→            elif \"processing_time\" in name:\n   583→                lower_bounds.append(0)\n   584→                upper_bounds.append(max(5000, abs(p) * 20))\n   585→            elif \"intercept\" in name:\n   586→                lower_bounds.append(p - abs(p) * 5 - 5000)\n   587→                upper_bounds.append(p + abs(p) * 5 + 5000)\n   588→            else:\n   589→                # Coefficients: allow sign flips\n   590→                lower_bounds.append(p - abs(p) * 5 - 100)\n   591→                upper_bounds.append(p + abs(p) * 5 + 100)\n   592→\n   593→        # CMA-ES sigma: 30% of initial magnitude or 100 for near-zero params\n   594→        sigma0 = max(100, 0.3 * np.mean(np.abs(initial_params[initial_params != 0])))\n   595→\n   596→        eval_count = 0\n   597→        convergence_log = []\n   598→\n   599→        def objective(params):\n   600→            \"\"\"Evaluate mean E2E error across experiments for this model.\"\"\"\n   601→            nonlocal eval_count\n   602→            eval_count += 1\n   603→\n   604→            # Reconstruct artifact\n   605→            artifact = param_vector_to_artifact(params, param_names, base_artifact)\n   606→            art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"cma_{canonical_model}_{eval_count}.json\")\n   607→            with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   608→                json.dump(artifact, f)\n   609→\n   610→            errors = []\n   611→            for exp in exps:\n   612→                csv_path, horizon_us = trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]]\n   613→                blis = run_blis_trace(\n   614→                    csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   615→                    horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   616→                )\n   617→                if blis is None:\n   618→                    errors.append(5.0)  # Penalty for failed runs\n   619→                else:\n   620→                    e2e_err = compute_error(\n   621→                        blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000\n   622→                    )\n   623→                    errors.append(e2e_err)\n   624→\n   625→            os.unlink(art_path)\n   626→            mean_err = np.mean(errors)\n   627→            convergence_log.append({\"eval\": eval_count, \"mean_e2e_error\": float(mean_err)})\n   628→\n   629→            if eval_count % 10 == 0:\n   630→                print(f\"    Eval {eval_count}: mean E2E error = {mean_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   631→\n   632→            return mean_err\n   633→\n   634→        # Run CMA-ES\n   635→        opts = cma.CMAOptions()\n   636→        opts[\"maxfevals\"] = 150  # Budget: 150 evaluations per model\n   637→        opts[\"timeout\"] = 1800  # 30 min timeout per model\n   638→        opts[\"bounds\"] = [lower_bounds, upper_bounds]\n   639→        opts[\"verbose\"] = -1  # Suppress CMA output\n   640→        opts[\"seed\"] = 42\n   641→        opts[\"popsize\"] = 8  # Small population for fast iteration\n   642→\n   643→        t0 = time.time()\n   644→        es = cma.CMAEvolutionStrategy(initial_params.tolist(), sigma0, opts)\n   645→        es.optimize(objective)\n   646→        elapsed = time.time() - t0\n   647→\n   648→        best_params = es.result.xbest\n   649→        best_error = es.result.fbest\n   650→        print(f\"  CMA-ES done in {elapsed:.0f}s, {eval_count} evals\")\n   651→        print(f\"  Best mean E2E error: {best_error*100:.1f}%\")\n   652→\n   653→        # Build optimized artifact\n   654→        optimized_art = param_vector_to_artifact(best_params, param_names, base_artifact)\n   655→        optimized_artifacts[canonical_model] = optimized_art\n   656→\n   657→        # Log parameter changes\n   658→        param_changes = {}\n   659→        for name, old, new in zip(param_names, initial_params, best_params):\n   660→            pct_change = ((new - old) / abs(old) * 100) if old != 0 else (new * 100 if new != 0 else 0)\n   661→            param_changes[name] = {\n   662→                \"initial\": float(old), \"optimized\": float(new),\n   663→                \"pct_change\": float(pct_change),\n   664→            }\n   665→\n   666→        optimization_logs[canonical_model] = {\n   667→            \"n_evals\": eval_count,\n   668→            \"elapsed_s\": elapsed,\n   669→            \"initial_mean_e2e\": float(np.mean([\n   670→                initial_results.get(e[\"dirname\"], {}).get(\"e2e_error\", 1.0)\n   671→                for e in exps\n   672→            ])),\n   673→            \"best_mean_e2e\": float(best_error),\n   674→            \"param_changes\": param_changes,\n   675→            \"convergence\": convergence_log,\n   676→        }\n   677→\n   678→    # Final evaluation with optimized artifacts\n   679→    print(\"\\n--- Final Evaluation (Optimized) ---\")\n   680→    h1_results = []\n   681→    for exp in experiments:\n   682→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   683→        # Find canonical model\n   684→        canonical = model\n   685→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   686→            if model in variants:\n   687→                canonical = group_key\n   688→                break\n   689→\n   690→        optimized_art = optimized_artifacts.get(canonical)\n   691→        if optimized_art is None:\n   692→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: NO OPTIMIZED ARTIFACT\")\n   693→            continue\n   694→\n   695→        # For grouped models (llama-2-70b variants), need to use the right base artifact\n   696→        if model != canonical and model in MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP:\n   697→            # Load the variant's base artifact and apply the same parameter changes\n   698→            variant_base = load_artifact(model)\n   699→            variant_params, variant_names = artifact_to_param_vector(variant_base)\n   700→            # Apply the same relative changes from canonical optimization\n   701→            canon_base = load_artifact(canonical)\n   702→            canon_initial, canon_names = artifact_to_param_vector(canon_base)\n   703→            canon_optimized, _ = artifact_to_param_vector(optimized_art)\n   704→\n   705→            # Apply proportional changes\n   706→            new_params = np.copy(variant_params)\n   707→            for i, name in enumerate(variant_names):\n   708→                if i < len(canon_names) and name == canon_names[i]:\n   709→                    if canon_initial[i] != 0:\n   710→                        ratio = canon_optimized[i] / canon_initial[i]\n   711→                        new_params[i] = variant_params[i] * ratio\n   712→                    else:\n   713→                        new_params[i] = canon_optimized[i]\n   714→            art_to_use = param_vector_to_artifact(new_params, variant_names, variant_base)\n   715→        else:\n   716→            art_to_use = optimized_art\n   717→\n   718→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"final_{exp['dirname']}.json\")\n   719→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   720→            json.dump(art_to_use, f)\n   721→\n   722→        csv_path, horizon_us = trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]]\n   723→        blis = run_blis_trace(\n   724→            csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   725→            horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   726→        )\n   727→\n   728→        if blis:\n   729→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   730→            ttft_err = compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   731→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   732→\n   733→            # Get initial for comparison\n   734→            init = initial_results.get(exp[\"dirname\"], {})\n   735→            init_e2e = init.get(\"e2e_error\", 1.0) * 100\n   736→\n   737→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}% (was {init_e2e:.1f}%), \"\n   738→                  f\"TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   739→\n   740→            h1_results.append({\n   741→                \"experiment\": exp[\"dirname\"],\n   742→                \"model\": model,\n   743→                \"workload\": exp[\"meta\"][\"workload\"],\n   744→                \"tp\": exp[\"meta\"][\"tp\"],\n   745→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   746→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   747→                \"gt_itl_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   748→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   749→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n   750→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   751→                \"blis_completed\": blis[\"completed_requests\"],\n   752→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   753→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   754→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   755→                \"initial_e2e_error\": init.get(\"e2e_error\", None),\n   756→            })\n   757→\n   758→        # Save the optimized artifact for this experiment\n   759→        final_art_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h1-trace-e2e-opt\", \"artifacts\")\n   760→        os.makedirs(final_art_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   761→        final_art_path = os.path.join(final_art_dir, f\"{model}_optimized.json\")\n   762→        with open(final_art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   763→            json.dump(art_to_use, f, indent=2)\n   764→\n   765→    return h1_results, initial_results, optimization_logs, optimized_artifacts\n   766→\n   767→\n   768→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   769→# H2: Workload-spec mode E2E optimization\n   770→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   771→def run_h2(experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir):\n   772→    \"\"\"H2: Run optimized artifacts in workload-spec mode.\"\"\"\n   773→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   774→    print(\"H2: Workload-Spec Mode with E2E-Optimized Coefficients\")\n   775→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   776→\n   777→    h2_results = []\n   778→\n   779→    for exp in experiments:\n   780→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   781→        dirname = exp[\"dirname\"]\n   782→\n   783→        # Find canonical model\n   784→        canonical = model\n   785→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   786→            if model in variants:\n   787→                canonical = group_key\n   788→                break\n   789→\n   790→        # Try to load profile from original eval directory\n   791→        orig_dir = os.path.join(ORIG_GT_ROOT, dirname)\n   792→        profile = load_profile(orig_dir) if os.path.isdir(orig_dir) else None\n   793→        if profile is None:\n   794→            profile = load_profile(exp[\"dirpath\"])\n   795→        if profile is None:\n   796→            print(f\"  {dirname}: SKIP (no profile)\")\n   797→            continue\n   798→\n   799→        # Build workload spec\n   800→        spec = build_workload_spec(profile, exp[\"gt\"])\n   801→        spec_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{dirname}_spec.yaml\")\n   802→        with open(spec_path, \"w\") as f:\n   803→            yaml.dump(spec, f, default_flow_style=False)\n   804→\n   805→        # Use the same optimized artifact from H1\n   806→        optimized_art = optimized_artifacts.get(canonical)\n   807→        if optimized_art is None:\n   808→            print(f\"  {dirname}: NO OPTIMIZED ARTIFACT\")\n   809→            continue\n   810→\n   811→        # Handle variant models\n   812→        if model != canonical and model in MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP:\n   813→            variant_base = load_artifact(model)\n   814→            variant_params, variant_names = artifact_to_param_vector(variant_base)\n   815→            canon_base = load_artifact(canonical)\n   816→            canon_initial, canon_names = artifact_to_param_vector(canon_base)\n   817→            canon_optimized, _ = artifact_to_param_vector(optimized_art)\n   818→            new_params = np.copy(variant_params)\n   819→            for i, name in enumerate(variant_names):\n   820→                if i < len(canon_names) and name == canon_names[i]:\n   821→                    if canon_initial[i] != 0:\n   822→                        new_params[i] = variant_params[i] * (canon_optimized[i] / canon_initial[i])\n   823→                    else:\n   824→                        new_params[i] = canon_optimized[i]\n   825→            art_to_use = param_vector_to_artifact(new_params, variant_names, variant_base)\n   826→        else:\n   827→            art_to_use = optimized_art\n   828→\n   829→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"h2_{dirname}.json\")\n   830→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   831→            json.dump(art_to_use, f)\n   832→\n   833→        blis = run_blis_workload_spec(\n   834→            spec_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   835→            exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   836→        )\n   837→\n   838→        if blis:\n   839→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   840→            ttft_err = compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   841→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   842→            print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%, TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   843→\n   844→            h2_results.append({\n   845→                \"experiment\": dirname,\n   846→                \"model\": model,\n   847→                \"workload\": exp[\"meta\"][\"workload\"],\n   848→                \"tp\": exp[\"meta\"][\"tp\"],\n   849→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   850→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   851→                \"gt_itl_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   852→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   853→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n   854→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   855→                \"blis_completed\": blis[\"completed_requests\"],\n   856→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   857→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   858→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   859→            })\n   860→        else:\n   861→            print(f\"  {dirname}: BLIS FAILED\")\n   862→\n   863→    return h2_results\n   864→\n   865→\n   866→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   867→# H3: Additive correction factors\n   868→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   869→def run_h3(h1_results, experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir):\n   870→    \"\"\"H3: Test additive/multiplicative correction factors on TTFT and ITL.\"\"\"\n   871→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   872→    print(\"H3: Additive Correction Factors\")\n   873→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   874→\n   875→    if not h1_results:\n   876→        print(\"  SKIP: No H1 results to compute corrections from.\")\n   877→        return [], {}\n   878→\n   879→    # Compute TTFT and ITL residuals per model\n   880→    model_residuals = {}\n   881→    for r in h1_results:\n   882→        model = r[\"model\"]\n   883→        if model not in model_residuals:\n   884→            model_residuals[model] = {\"ttft\": [], \"itl\": [], \"gt_ttft\": [], \"gt_itl\": []}\n   885→        model_residuals[model][\"ttft\"].append(r[\"blis_ttft_ms\"] - r[\"gt_ttft_ms\"])\n   886→        model_residuals[model][\"itl\"].append(r[\"blis_itl_ms\"] - r[\"gt_itl_ms\"])\n   887→        model_residuals[model][\"gt_ttft\"].append(r[\"gt_ttft_ms\"])\n   888→        model_residuals[model][\"gt_itl\"].append(r[\"gt_itl_ms\"])\n   889→\n   890→    # Compute correction factors per model\n   891→    corrections = {}\n   892→    print(\"\\n--- Residual Analysis ---\")\n   893→    for model, resid in model_residuals.items():\n   894→        ttft_residuals = np.array(resid[\"ttft\"])\n   895→        itl_residuals = np.array(resid[\"itl\"])\n   896→        gt_ttft = np.array(resid[\"gt_ttft\"])\n   897→        gt_itl = np.array(resid[\"gt_itl\"])\n   898→\n   899→        # TTFT correction: blis_ttft = alpha * gt_ttft + beta\n   900→        # We want corrected = blis / alpha - beta/alpha\n   901→        # But simpler: compute additive offset = mean(gt_ttft - blis_ttft)\n   902→        ttft_offset = float(np.mean(-ttft_residuals))  # Add this to blis_ttft\n   903→        # Multiplicative: gt / blis ratio\n   904→        blis_ttft_arr = gt_ttft + ttft_residuals  # = blis_ttft\n   905→        ttft_ratio = float(np.mean(gt_ttft / np.maximum(blis_ttft_arr, 0.01)))\n   906→\n   907→        # ITL correction\n   908→        itl_offset = float(np.mean(-itl_residuals))\n   909→        blis_itl_arr = gt_itl + itl_residuals\n   910→        itl_ratio = float(np.mean(gt_itl / np.maximum(blis_itl_arr, 0.01)))\n   911→\n   912→        corrections[model] = {\n   913→            \"ttft_additive_ms\": ttft_offset,\n   914→            \"ttft_multiplicative\": ttft_ratio,\n   915→            \"itl_additive_ms\": itl_offset,\n   916→            \"itl_multiplicative\": itl_ratio,\n   917→            \"ttft_residual_mean_ms\": float(np.mean(ttft_residuals)),\n   918→            \"ttft_residual_std_ms\": float(np.std(ttft_residuals)),\n   919→            \"itl_residual_mean_ms\": float(np.mean(itl_residuals)),\n   920→            \"itl_residual_std_ms\": float(np.std(itl_residuals)),\n   921→        }\n   922→        print(f\"  {model}: TTFT residual={np.mean(ttft_residuals):.1f}±{np.std(ttft_residuals):.1f}ms, \"\n   923→              f\"ITL residual={np.mean(itl_residuals):.2f}±{np.std(itl_residuals):.2f}ms\")\n   924→        print(f\"    TTFT correction: additive={ttft_offset:.1f}ms, multiplicative={ttft_ratio:.2f}x\")\n   925→        print(f\"    ITL correction: additive={itl_offset:.2f}ms, multiplicative={itl_ratio:.2f}x\")\n   926→\n   927→    # Apply corrections via QueueingTime and OutputTokenProcessingTime adjustments\n   928→    print(\"\\n--- Applying Corrections ---\")\n   929→    # Strategy: increase step_overhead_us (the main knob controlling E2E under-prediction)\n   930→    # and adjust queueing_time intercept (controls TTFT)\n   931→    h3_results = []\n   932→\n   933→    for exp in experiments:\n   934→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   935→        dirname = exp[\"dirname\"]\n   936→\n   937→        canonical = model\n   938→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   939→            if model in variants:\n   940→                canonical = group_key\n   941→                break\n   942→\n   943→        optimized_art = optimized_artifacts.get(canonical)\n   944→        if optimized_art is None:\n   945→            continue\n   946→\n   947→        # Get the artifact to use (handling variants)\n   948→        if model != canonical and model in MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP:\n   949→            variant_base = load_artifact(model)\n   950→            variant_params, variant_names = artifact_to_param_vector(variant_base)\n   951→            canon_base = load_artifact(canonical)\n   952→            canon_initial, canon_names = artifact_to_param_vector(canon_base)\n   953→            canon_optimized, _ = artifact_to_param_vector(optimized_art)\n   954→            new_params = np.copy(variant_params)\n   955→            for i, name in enumerate(variant_names):\n   956→                if i < len(canon_names) and name == canon_names[i]:\n   957→                    if canon_initial[i] != 0:\n   958→                        new_params[i] = variant_params[i] * (canon_optimized[i] / canon_initial[i])\n   959→                    else:\n   960→                        new_params[i] = canon_optimized[i]\n   961→            corrected_art = param_vector_to_artifact(new_params, variant_names, variant_base)\n   962→        else:\n   963→            corrected_art = copy.deepcopy(optimized_art)\n   964→\n   965→        # Apply TTFT correction: increase queueing time intercept\n   966→        corr = corrections.get(model, corrections.get(canonical, {}))\n   967→        ttft_add = corr.get(\"ttft_additive_ms\", 0) * 1000  # Convert ms → us\n   968→        if corrected_art.get(\"queueing_time\"):\n   969→            corrected_art[\"queueing_time\"][\"intercept\"] += ttft_add\n   970→        else:\n   971→            corrected_art[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   972→                \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   973→                \"intercept\": ttft_add,\n   974→                \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   975→            }\n   976→\n   977→        # Apply ITL correction: adjust output_token_processing_time\n   978→        itl_add = corr.get(\"itl_additive_ms\", 0) * 1000  # ms → us\n   979→        corrected_art[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"] = max(\n   980→            0, corrected_art.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0) + itl_add\n   981→        )\n   982→\n   983→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"h3_{dirname}.json\")\n   984→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   985→            json.dump(corrected_art, f)\n   986→\n   987→        csv_path, horizon_us = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{dirname}_trace.csv\"), None\n   988→        # Recompute horizon\n   989→        with open(exp[\"lifecycle_path\"]) as f:\n   990→            lc_data = json.load(f)\n   991→        arrivals = [e[\"start_time\"] for e in lc_data]\n   992→        duration_s = max(arrivals) - min(arrivals)\n   993→        horizon_us = int((duration_s + 120) * 1_000_000)\n   994→\n   995→        blis = run_blis_trace(\n   996→            csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   997→            horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   998→        )\n   999→\n  1000→        if blis:\n  1001→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n  1002→            ttft_err = compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n  1003→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n  1004→\n  1005→            # Get H1 baseline for comparison\n  1006→            h1_match = [r for r in h1_results if r[\"experiment\"] == dirname]\n  1007→            h1_e2e = h1_match[0][\"e2e_error\"] * 100 if h1_match else None\n  1008→\n  1009→            print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%\"\n  1010→                  + (f\" (H1: {h1_e2e:.1f}%)\" if h1_e2e else \"\")\n  1011→                  + f\", TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n  1012→\n  1013→            h3_results.append({\n  1014→                \"experiment\": dirname,\n  1015→                \"model\": model,\n  1016→                \"workload\": exp[\"meta\"][\"workload\"],\n  1017→                \"tp\": exp[\"meta\"][\"tp\"],\n  1018→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n  1019→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n  1020→                \"gt_itl_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n  1021→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n  1022→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n  1023→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n  1024→                \"blis_completed\": blis[\"completed_requests\"],\n  1025→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n  1026→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n  1027→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n  1028→                \"h1_e2e_error\": h1_match[0][\"e2e_error\"] if h1_match else None,\n  1029→            })\n  1030→\n  1031→    return h3_results, corrections\n  1032→\n  1033→\n  1034→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1035→# Main\n  1036→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1037→def write_results_csv(results, path):\n  1038→    if not results:\n  1039→        return\n  1040→    all_keys = set()\n  1041→    for r in results:\n  1042→        all_keys.update(r.keys())\n  1043→    fieldnames = sorted(all_keys)\n  1044→    with open(path, \"w\", newline=\"\") as f:\n  1045→        writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n  1046→        writer.writeheader()\n  1047→        writer.writerows(results)\n  1048→\n  1049→\n  1050→def main():\n  1051→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n  1052→    print(\"Round 3, Idea 3: E2E Calibration via Direct E2E Objective\")\n  1053→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n  1054→\n  1055→    # Ensure binary exists\n  1056→    if not os.path.isfile(BINARY_PATH):\n  1057→        print(\"Building simulation_worker...\")\n  1058→        build = subprocess.run(\n  1059→            [\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", BINARY_PATH, \"main.go\"],\n  1060→            cwd=REPO_ROOT, capture_output=True, text=True,\n  1061→        )\n  1062→        if build.returncode != 0:\n  1063→            print(f\"Build failed: {build.stderr}\", file=sys.stderr)\n  1064→            sys.exit(1)\n  1065→\n  1066→    experiments = discover_experiments()\n  1067→    print(f\"\\nFound {len(experiments)} experiments with lifecycle data.\")\n  1068→\n  1069→    if not experiments:\n  1070→        print(\"ERROR: No experiments found!\", file=sys.stderr)\n  1071→        sys.exit(1)\n  1072→\n  1073→    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n  1074→        # H1: CMA-ES with trace replay\n  1075→        h1_results, initial_results, opt_logs, optimized_artifacts = run_h1(experiments, tmpdir)\n  1076→\n  1077→        # H2: Workload-spec mode with optimized coefficients\n  1078→        h2_results = run_h2(experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir)\n  1079→\n  1080→        # H3: Additive correction factors\n  1081→        h3_results, corrections = run_h3(h1_results, experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir)\n  1082→\n  1083→    # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1084→    # Write all results\n  1085→    # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1086→    h1_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h1-trace-e2e-opt\")\n  1087→    h2_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h2-workload-spec-opt\")\n  1088→    h3_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h3-additive-corrections\")\n  1089→\n  1090→    os.makedirs(h1_dir, exist_ok=True)\n  1091→    os.makedirs(h2_dir, exist_ok=True)\n  1092→    os.makedirs(h3_dir, exist_ok=True)\n  1093→\n  1094→    # H1 outputs\n  1095→    write_results_csv(h1_results, os.path.join(h1_dir, \"e2e_opt_results.csv\"))\n  1096→    if h1_results:\n  1097→        ok = [r for r in h1_results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1098→        h1_summary = {\n  1099→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n  1100→            \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1101→            \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1102→            \"mean_itl_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1103→            \"e2e_under_10pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10),\n  1104→            \"e2e_under_15pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.15),\n  1105→            \"e2e_under_25pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.25),\n  1106→            \"initial_mean_e2e_pct\": np.mean([\n  1107→                initial_results.get(r[\"experiment\"], {}).get(\"e2e_error\", 1.0)\n  1108→                for r in ok\n  1109→            ]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1110→            \"optimization_logs\": opt_logs,\n  1111→            \"per_experiment\": ok,\n  1112→        }\n  1113→        with open(os.path.join(h1_dir, \"summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n  1114→            json.dump(h1_summary, f, indent=2)\n  1115→\n  1116→    # H2 outputs\n  1117→    write_results_csv(h2_results, os.path.join(h2_dir, \"workload_spec_results.csv\"))\n  1118→    if h2_results:\n  1119→        ok = [r for r in h2_results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1120→        h2_summary = {\n  1121→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n  1122→            \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1123→            \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1124→            \"mean_itl_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1125→            \"e2e_under_50pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.50),\n  1126→            \"per_experiment\": ok,\n  1127→        }\n  1128→        with open(os.path.join(h2_dir, \"summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n  1129→            json.dump(h2_summary, f, indent=2)\n  1130→\n  1131→    # H3 outputs\n  1132→    write_results_csv(h3_results, os.path.join(h3_dir, \"correction_results.csv\"))\n  1133→    if h3_results:\n  1134→        ok = [r for r in h3_results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1135→        h3_summary = {\n  1136→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n  1137→            \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1138→            \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1139→            \"mean_itl_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1140→            \"corrections\": corrections,\n  1141→            \"per_experiment\": ok,\n  1142→        }\n  1143→        with open(os.path.join(h3_dir, \"summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n  1144→            json.dump(h3_summary, f, indent=2)\n  1145→\n  1146→    # Print final summary\n  1147→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n  1148→    print(\"FINAL SUMMARY\")\n  1149→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n  1150→\n  1151→    for label, results in [(\"H1 (trace+CMA-ES)\", h1_results),\n  1152→                           (\"H2 (workload-spec)\", h2_results),\n  1153→                           (\"H3 (corrections)\", h3_results)]:\n  1154→        ok = [r for r in results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1155→        if ok:\n  1156→            mean_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100\n  1157→            mean_ttft = np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100\n  1158→            mean_itl = np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100\n  1159→            under_10 = sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10)\n  1160→            print(f\"\\n{label}: E2E={mean_e2e:.1f}%, TTFT={mean_ttft:.1f}%, \"\n  1161→                  f\"ITL={mean_itl:.1f}%, E2E<10%={under_10}/{len(ok)}\")\n  1162→        else:\n  1163→            print(f\"\\n{label}: No results\")\n  1164→\n  1165→    print(\"\\nDone!\")\n  1166→\n  1167→\n  1168→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n  1169→    main()\n  1170→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YDgwzYnaKyFjGGak7aDXLb","session_id":"c72182bb-90d4-4f72-be1e-6f3d8138bce2","uuid":"5d8c0b8c-9349-4c88-b0d7-6a681ec70e7d"}
