{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YDgwzYnaKyFjGGak7aDXLb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile the final report.\n\n---\n\n## Search Results: Round 3 CMA-ES Experiment Code and FINDINGS\n\n### 1. Location of Round 3 Files\n\nRound 3 artifacts do **NOT** exist in the current worktree (`round4-idea-1-constrained-cmaes`) or on the `stepml-experiments` branch. They exist only in the **main BLIS-research repo** at:\n\n```\n/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/\n```\n\nNo `round2/` or `round3/` directories were ever committed to the `stepml-experiments` branch. The worktree only has `round1/` and `round4/`.\n\n### 2. Complete List of R3 Experiment Files\n\n**Round 3 top level:**\n- `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/FINDINGS_ROUND3.md`\n- `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/research.md`\n- `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/STATUS`\n- `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/.phase1_done`\n- Log files: `phase1_wp1_wp2.log`, `phase2_idea-1-trace-replay.log`, `phase2_idea-2-total-context-model.log`, `phase2_idea-3-e2e-calibration.log`, `phase_final_wp4.log`\n\n**Idea 1 (Trace Replay):**\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/run_experiment.py` (28,159 bytes)\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/HYPOTHESIS.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/REPRODUCE.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/GENERALIZATION_NOTE.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/go_changes.patch`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/stepml_cli_integration.patch`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/h1-trace-replay/FINDINGS.md`, `summary.json`, `trace_replay_results.csv`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/h2-error-attribution/FINDINGS.md`, `summary.json`, `error_attribution.csv`\n- `.../round3/idea-1-trace-replay/h3-workload-diagnosis/FINDINGS.md`\n\n**Idea 2 (Total-Context Model):**\n- `.../round3/idea-2-total-context-model/run_h1_h2.py` (22,619 bytes)\n- `.../round3/idea-2-total-context-model/run_h3_blis.py` (21,098 bytes)\n- `.../round3/idea-2-total-context-model/run_generalization.py` (15,333 bytes)\n- `.../round3/idea-2-total-context-model/HYPOTHESIS.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-2-total-context-model/FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-2-total-context-model/REPRODUCE.md`\n- Sub-hypothesis outputs: `h1-fairbatching-formulation/`, `h2-feature-scaling/`, `h3-blis-e2e-34b/`, `h4-lowo-generalization/`, `h5-lomo-generalization/`\n\n**Idea 3 (CMA-ES -- the key one):**\n- `.../round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/run_experiment.py` **(47,530 bytes -- the main CMA-ES code)**\n- `.../round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/run_generalization.py` (22,454 bytes -- LOMO/LOWO evaluation)\n- `.../round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/HYPOTHESIS.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/REPRODUCE.md`\n- `.../round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/go_changes.patch`\n- **Optimized artifacts** (JSON, per-model):\n  - `.../h1-trace-e2e-opt/artifacts/llama-2-7b_optimized.json`\n  - `.../h1-trace-e2e-opt/artifacts/llama-2-70b_optimized.json`\n  - `.../h1-trace-e2e-opt/artifacts/llama-2-70b-hf_optimized.json`\n  - `.../h1-trace-e2e-opt/artifacts/codellama-34b_optimized.json`\n  - `.../h1-trace-e2e-opt/artifacts/mixtral-8x7b-v0-1_optimized.json`\n- `.../h1-trace-e2e-opt/FINDINGS.md`, `e2e_opt_results.csv`, `summary.json`\n- `.../h2-workload-spec-opt/FINDINGS.md`\n- `.../h3-additive-corrections/FINDINGS.md`, `correction_results.csv`, `summary.json`\n- `.../h4-lowo-generalization/FINDINGS.md`, `HYPOTHESIS.md`, `output/h4_results.json`\n- `.../h5-lomo-generalization/FINDINGS.md`, `HYPOTHESIS.md`, `output/h5_results.json`\n\n### 3. CMA-ES Python Code -- Key Portions\n\nThe main CMA-ES code is in `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/run_experiment.py` (1,170 lines).\n\n**CMA-ES configuration** (lines 635-644):\n```python\nopts = cma.CMAOptions()\nopts[\"maxfevals\"] = 150  # Budget: 150 evaluations per model\nopts[\"timeout\"] = 1800   # 30 min timeout per model\nopts[\"bounds\"] = [lower_bounds, upper_bounds]\nopts[\"verbose\"] = -1\nopts[\"seed\"] = 42\nopts[\"popsize\"] = 8      # Small population for fast iteration\n```\n\n**Objective function** (lines 599-632) -- single-objective E2E only, no ITL penalty:\n```python\ndef objective(params):\n    nonlocal eval_count\n    eval_count += 1\n    artifact = param_vector_to_artifact(params, param_names, base_artifact)\n    # Write artifact, run BLIS for each experiment\n    errors = []\n    for exp in exps:\n        blis = run_blis_trace(csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], ...)\n        if blis is None:\n            errors.append(5.0)  # Penalty for failed runs\n        else:\n            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n            errors.append(e2e_err)\n    mean_err = np.mean(errors)\n    return mean_err  # <-- ONLY E2E, no ITL term\n```\n\n**Parameter vector** (lines 229-284) -- 14-23 parameters per model:\n- `step_overhead_us`, `step_overhead_per_req_us`\n- `scheduling_processing_time_us`, `preemption_processing_time_us`\n- `output_token_processing_time_us`\n- `queueing_intercept`\n- Per-regime coefficients: `decode_only_intercept`, `decode_only_decode_tokens`, `decode_only_num_decode_reqs`, `mixed_intercept`, `mixed_prefill_tokens`, `mixed_decode_tokens`, `mixed_num_prefill_reqs`, `mixed_num_decode_reqs`, etc.\n\n**Bounds** (lines 575-591) -- very wide, essentially unconstrained:\n```python\nif \"overhead\" in name and \"per_req\" not in name:\n    lower_bounds.append(max(500, p * 0.3))\n    upper_bounds.append(p * 5.0)\nelif \"processing_time\" in name:\n    lower_bounds.append(0)\n    upper_bounds.append(max(5000, abs(p) * 20))  # <-- allows 0 to 5000+\nelif \"intercept\" in name:\n    lower_bounds.append(p - abs(p) * 5 - 5000)\n    upper_bounds.append(p + abs(p) * 5 + 5000)\n```\n\n**Optimized artifact example** (llama-2-7b):\n```json\n{\n  \"step_overhead_us\": 5051.28,\n  \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 1899.06,  // <-- implausibly large\n  \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 554.39,\n  \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 254.17,\n  \"step_overhead_per_req_us\": 97.60,\n  \"step_time_regimes\": [\n    {\"name\": \"decode_only\", \"model\": {\"intercept\": 544.22, ...}},\n    {\"name\": \"mixed_light\", \"model\": {\"intercept\": -705.36, ...}}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 4. eval/ground_truth Experiment Directories\n\nThe `eval/ground_truth/` directory does **NOT** exist in the worktree or on the `stepml-experiments` branch. It exists in the BLIS-research repo at:\n\n```\n/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/eval/ground_truth/\n```\n\n**10 experiment directories** (each with `results/`, `exp-config.yaml`, `vllm.log`, `profile.yaml`):\n\n| Directory | Model | TP | Workload |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `20260217-162547-llama-2-7b-tp1-roleplay` | llama-2-7b | 1 | roleplay |\n| `20260217-202857-llama-2-70b-tp4-general` | llama-2-70b | 4 | general |\n| `20260217-203421-llama-2-70b-hf-tp4-codegen` | llama-2-70b-hf | 4 | codegen |\n| `20260218-084319-llama-2-70b-tp4-roleplay` | llama-2-70b | 4 | roleplay |\n| `20260218-120914-mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-codegen` | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 2 | codegen |\n| `20260218-130541-mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-general` | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 2 | general |\n| `20260218-141024-mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-roleplay` | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 2 | roleplay |\n| `20260218-150304-codellama-34b-tp2-general` | codellama-34b | 2 | general |\n| `20260218-150956-codellama-34b-tp2-codegen` | codellama-34b | 2 | codegen |\n| `20260218-155500-codellama-34b-tp2-roleplay` | codellama-34b | 2 | roleplay |\n\nAlso has `SCHEMA.md` describing the directory format.\n\n### 5. R3 FINDINGS Summary -- CMA-ES Parameters and Results\n\n**Key CMA-ES results from R3:**\n\n| Model | Initial E2E | Optimized E2E | Evals | Time | Key Change |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| llama-2-7b | 60.9% | 22.2% | 152 | 801s | `step_overhead_us`: 3,897 -> 5,051 (+30%) |\n| llama-2-70b | 62.7% | 8.3% | 96 | 1,904s | `scheduling_time`: 415 -> 821 (+98%) |\n| mixtral-8x7b | 52.2% | 25.9% | 96 | 1,870s | `step_overhead_us`: 9,125 -> 9,884 (+8%) |\n| codellama-34b | 58.9% | 7.9% | 96 | 1,913s | `step_overhead_us`: 6,673 -> 5,998 (-10%) |\n\n**Overall R3 CMA-ES: 15.1% mean E2E, 87.4% mean ITL, 4/10 < 10% E2E**\n\n**Critical problem for R4:** The unconstrained single-objective CMA-ES inflated `output_token_processing_time_us` to implausible values (e.g., llama-2-7b: 0 -> 1,899 us). This is the root cause of the 87.4% ITL degradation. R4 Idea 1 (constrained CMA-ES) directly addresses this by adding ITL penalty terms and parameter bounds (OTPT bounded to [0, 500]).\n\n**LOMO generalization:** Mean best-donor E2E = **14.8%** (cross-model transfer). Mixtral is best universal donor (11.9-26.0%). 70B -> Mixtral transfer achieves 5.1% (better than Mixtral's own 25.9%).\n\n**LOWO generalization:** Dense models generalize well (9-16pp range). Mixtral has highest workload variance (21.5pp). 8/10 within 2x of aggregate."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6464de (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 6346\ntool_uses: 45\nduration_ms: 162666</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c72182bb-90d4-4f72-be1e-6f3d8138bce2","uuid":"e585cede-e800-4185-9d90-aa18d4c59474","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find prior Round 3 CMA-ES experiment code and any FINDINGS documents. Search thoroughly in these locations:\n1. hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/ 